identity /aɪˈdɛntɪtɪ/

(identities) 

1. N-COUNT Your identity is who you are. 身份 

例： Abu is not his real name, but it's one he uses to disguise his identity. 阿布不是他的真名，而是一个他用来掩盖自己身份的假名。 

2. N-VAR The identity of a person or place is the characteristics that distinguish them from others. 特性 

例： I wanted a sense of my own identity. 我需要确立自身的个性意识。

